---
dops: v1
kind: tool

meta:
  name: docker-compose
  version: 1.0.0
  description: "Generate Docker Compose service definitions"
  author: dojops
  license: MIT
  tags: [docker, compose, container, service, orchestration]

input:
  fields:
    projectPath:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Root directory of the project"
    services:
      type: string
      required: true
      description: "Description of services to define"
    networkMode:
      type: enum
      values: [bridge, host, none]
      default: bridge
    environment:
      type: string

output:
  type: object
  required: [services]
  properties:
    services:
      type: object
      description: "Service definitions"
    networks:
      type: object
      description: "Network definitions"
    volumes:
      type: object
      description: "Volume definitions"

files:
  - path: "{projectPath}/docker-compose.yml"
    format: yaml
    source: llm
    options:
      sortKeys: false
      lineWidth: 120

detection:
  paths: ["docker-compose.yml", "docker-compose.yaml", "compose.yml", "compose.yaml"]
  updateMode: true

verification:
  structural:
    - path: "services"
      required: true
      type: object
      message: "Services section is required"

  binary:
    command: "docker compose -f docker-compose.yml config"
    parser: docker-compose-config
    timeout: 30000
    cwd: output

permissions:
  filesystem: write
  child_process: required
  network: none

scope:
  write: ["{projectPath}/docker-compose.yml"]

risk:
  level: MEDIUM
  rationale: "Service stack changes affect running containers"

execution:
  mode: generate
  deterministic: false
  idempotent: true

update:
  strategy: replace
  inputSource: file
  injectAs: existingContent
---
# Docker Compose

## Prompt

You are a Docker Compose expert. Generate Docker Compose service definitions as structured JSON.

Respond with a JSON object matching the Docker Compose structure:
{
  "services": {
    "web": {
      "image": "nginx:1.25",
      "ports": ["80:80"],
      "volumes": ["./html:/usr/share/nginx/html"],
      "restart": "unless-stopped"
    },
    "db": {
      "image": "postgres:16",
      "environment": { "POSTGRES_PASSWORD": "changeme" },
      "volumes": ["db-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data"]
    }
  },
  "networks": {
    "default": { "driver": "bridge" }
  },
  "volumes": {
    "db-data": {}
  }
}

IMPORTANT:
- "services" is required with at least one service
- Each service should have "image" at minimum
- Use named volumes for data persistence
- Include "restart" policies for production services
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Update Prompt

You are a Docker Compose expert. Update the existing Docker Compose configuration.
Preserve existing services and settings. Only add/modify what is requested.

--- EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---
{existingContent}
--- END EXISTING CONFIGURATION ---

Respond with valid JSON containing the complete Docker Compose structure.

IMPORTANT:
- Preserve ALL existing services unless explicitly asked to remove them
- Maintain existing volume and network definitions
- Respond with valid JSON only, no markdown

## Examples

Given: "Web app with nginx, postgres database, and redis cache"

```json
{
  "services": {
    "web": {
      "image": "nginx:1.25",
      "ports": ["80:80"],
      "depends_on": ["app"],
      "restart": "unless-stopped"
    },
    "app": {
      "build": ".",
      "environment": {
        "DATABASE_URL": "postgres://user:pass@db:5432/app",
        "REDIS_URL": "redis://redis:6379"
      },
      "depends_on": ["db", "redis"]
    },
    "db": {
      "image": "postgres:16",
      "environment": { "POSTGRES_PASSWORD": "changeme" },
      "volumes": ["db-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data"]
    },
    "redis": {
      "image": "redis:7-alpine",
      "restart": "unless-stopped"
    }
  },
  "volumes": {
    "db-data": {}
  }
}
```

## Constraints

- Use specific image tags, not :latest
- Always include restart policies for production services
- Use named volumes for persistent data
- Define health checks for critical services
- Do not hardcode secrets — use environment variables
- Maximum 20 services per composition

## Keywords

docker, compose, docker-compose, container, service, microservice,
orchestration, multi-container, volume, network, build, deploy
